==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bifarious
<hw>Bi*fa"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bifarius</ets>; <ets>bis</ets> twice + <ets>fari</ets> to speak.
Cf. Gr. <?/ twofold; <?/ twice + <?/ to say.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Twofold; arranged in two rows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Pointing two ways, as leaves that
grow only on opposite sides of a branch; in two vertical rows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bifariously</ent>⟦br⟧
